---
import DemoComponentCard from '../../../../components/DemoComponentCard.astro';
---
<p class='text-body-large'>The button group supports two layout variants: <strong>standard</strong> (buttons with a gap) and <strong>connected</strong> (buttons joined together).</p>

<p class='text-body-large'><strong>Standard</strong> — buttons are independent with a visible gap between them.</p>
<DemoComponentCard lang={'html'}>
  <wc-button-group variant='standard'>
    <wc-button>First</wc-button>
    <wc-button>Second</wc-button>
    <wc-button>Third</wc-button>
  </wc-button-group>
</DemoComponentCard>

<p class='text-body-large'><strong>Connected</strong> — buttons share edges and form a single visual unit.</p>
<DemoComponentCard lang={'html'}>
  <wc-button-group variant='connected'>
    <wc-button>First</wc-button>
    <wc-button>Second</wc-button>
    <wc-button>Third</wc-button>
  </wc-button-group>
</DemoComponentCard>

<p class='text-body-large'>Connected variant also works with icon buttons.</p>
<DemoComponentCard lang={'html'}>
  <wc-button-group variant='connected'>
    <wc-icon-button name='format_bold'></wc-icon-button>
    <wc-icon-button name='format_italic'></wc-icon-button>
    <wc-icon-button name='format_underlined'></wc-icon-button>
  </wc-button-group>
</DemoComponentCard>

<style is:inline>
  strong {
    font-weight: bold;
  }
</style>
